    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><div n="1" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/>
                Heraclii </ab></div><div n="2" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/> Benignissimo viro princi<lb break="no" n="2"/>pali prudentissimo et integ&amp;lt;e=I&amp;gt;<expan><abbr>rr</abbr><ex>imo</ex></expan> <lb n="3"/><expan><abbr>T</abbr><ex>ito</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Fl</abbr><ex>avio</ex></expan> Frontino Heraclio <expan><abbr>v</abbr><ex>iro</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>p</abbr><ex>erfectissimo</ex></expan> au<lb break="no" n="4"/>guri sacerdoti <expan><abbr>Lauren</abbr><ex>tium</ex></expan> Labinat<expan><ex>i</ex><abbr>um</abbr></expan> <note>sic</note> <lb n="5"/>IIviro ob diversarum volup<lb break="no" n="6"/>tatum exhibitiones adque <lb n="7"/>admirabilem ludorum <lb n="8"/>editionem amoremque <lb n="9"/>incomparabilem in pa<lb break="no" n="10"/>triam et cives suos sufra<lb break="no" n="11"/>gio quietissimi populi <lb n="12"/>et decreto splendidis<lb break="no" n="13"/>simi ordinis 
            </ab></div></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>(B) AE 1929: Z. 3: integerr(imo); Z. 5: sacerdoti. The inscription is carved over an erased earlier text; a second erased text is on the right side. Datierung: spätkonstantinische Zeit.</p>
            </div>
